name: You Sunshine
review_text: This isn't the place to go if youre considering AF or a new gym. The vibe here is tense, and the staff can come across as overly authoritative. If you're looking for a more relaxed and positive environment, I'd recommend the central branch instead. It's not worth spending the extra money at this outlet, especially when the personal trainers seem unprofessional and disrespectful. You'd be better off finding a regular gym that offers better service and saves you money.

name: Lheng Lucea
review_text: closing time is extended compare to last time. this is more flexible to members. well done! for those staff that are aggressive i saw the comments, not all of them. maybe they are tired also. but all in all they are accomodating and friendly. sometimes we have to be more understanding and choose to be kind.

name: Ferhan Feroze
review_text: Luv the ambience and the equipment here.

name: Suriya Jaiphet
review_text: My recent visit to Fitness First was marred by lackluster customer service from the front desk staff and aggressive sales tactics from the sales team. The receptionist appeared disinterested, providing vague responses to my queries. The sales team resorted to high-pressure tactics, pushing for a quick decision without clear information. The gym environment felt more like a sales pitch than a welcoming fitness center. Overall, the experience was disappointing, with a focus on closing deals rather than prioritizing customer satisfaction. I left feeling uncomfortable and unlikely to return.

name: Yi Qian Goh
review_text: This branch does not provide gym attire. Do bring your own clothes.

name: Merciless
review_text: I gving 5* due to the staff working there, they are friendly and willing to help if you have queries. But let me tell you this: the place is small and crowded. If you wish to do your sets or reps, prepare some of them will hog the equipment until theres no tomorrow.

name: Jonathan Teo
review_text: Great gym with good equipments and good customer service too

name: Teewreckz
review_text: Hua Guan has been an amazing trainer and I dare say that I recommend anyone to look for him if you are looking to achieve your own personal fitness goals. He has been with me at every step of the way be it fitness or nutrition to make sure I am hitting my goals one step at a time; finetuning workouts to make sure sessions are not rigid and switching up meals so you do not have to stick to mundane meals all the time. I would give him 6 stars but too bad google review only allow 5 as the max.

name: Jonathan Tan
review_text: This outlet of Fitness First is one of the more spacious ones! Theres a good selection of machines, and there are 3 power racks! Which is great because I hate queuing for the barbell, plus I dont feel so pressured to finish my sets. This outlet doesnt offer workout attire though, and only towels. But for a gym in the hood and not in town, this is pretty well equipped.

review_text: Amazing environment and well equipped

name: Freddy Har
review_text: Join ff because of the polite staff but tampinese ff is opposite. Not only the staff is rude the management there also very rude. Hold back my cash card and not let me leave saying that I cannot bring visitor even if they give me the 3day pass for my friend, we have to wait 10min for the management to come out and warn me that I have to pay 35dollars if I didnt informed inadvance, this is the 2nd day I use the pass and first day already meet the staff with all explanation of the place at tampinese so I thought 2nd visit no need book again. I apologise and say ok nxt round I will book before I bring a friend with the 3day pass as I was given 3 passes but the staff insist of holding me back to finish all her talks, I suggest if want to do all this maybe can give a call and not holding me and my guest and also taking my cash card and not returning is really not right. After this case the staff that hold back my card would give me a fercie look whenever I use the gym in tampinese ff. Hope some changes can be done in tampinese ff. When to others ff and never had this problem before.

review_text: Wanted to get a one day trial of the place and forgot that i had like signed up for the trial la. Didnt go, and the lady called me a day after and kinda asked "whats the purpose of you going for the trial ah?" Sounded more like she didnt wanna let me go and just wanted to get ppl to immediately pay for it. LOL. Such a money grabber. I told her i am unemployed atm and also just wanted to try the gym but its ok sounds like this gym has issues anywayyy. Oh and i asked her "sorry? " cause i couldnt hear her and she just said thank u and put down the phone.... Erm sure?

name: Diana Peh (dp)
review_text:
Thx to staff who show me around for quick tour and try out for yoga last min!

Was greeted by the counter staff!

name: Anson Ke
review_text: Worst experience

name: Lydia K
review_text:
Good facilities with large cardio and strength area, large clean bathrooms and showers, and class studios. I only took 1 star away because the membership fees and sign up process were annoying.

First you have to meet a salesperson before theyll tell you the fees, and second you must pay an initiation fee which is the worst part of gym memberships.

The salesperson said to waive the initiation fee, I will have to sign up for personal training sessions and nutritional supplements. I chose that but the personal trainer assigned to me had a very bad attitude. I told him Id trained before (with my fiance) and he mocked my form. 2 years? Youve trained for 2 years and you still cant do a deadlift properly? Very annoying. Didnt try to make another appointment with him.

Classes are difficult to book unless you camp at your phone. I dont think I will sign up with Fitness First again.

name: Alexa Tan
review_text: One of the front desk lady has disgusting service attitude. I went to the gym and politely asked to claim a guest pass for my bf (as per the new rules) and she was seemingly annoyed by my request, raised her voice, demanded to know who my fitness consultant is and kept pressing me to contact my fitness consultant. She basically tried to push all her responsibility away. What a shame to meet a service staff that lacks basic courtesy. Also, facility is dirty. Equipments are often dusty (especially the plates), yoga studio smelled like sweaty feet the whole time, and there were even cockroaches in the shower. Imagine paying over $160 for standards worse than public gym. Needless to say I discontinued my membership. Please avoid at all costs.

name: Janet Ho
review_text: No pantry and no attire supply

name: chong faiyuen
review_text:
Pre-covid, I was with FF for more than 15 years. Then rejoined in 2022. Noticed the Yoga instructors' standards dropped , left only few good ones like Faiz , Chandra , Paul but they only teach 1-2 times a week. Rest of the instructors especially Albert Tan, Christine Tan classes are disappointing! You would not want to waste your time.
Feedback a few times to the club , hopefully will see improvements.

name: Christine Chong
review_text:
I tend to attend their yoga classes - can be hit or miss depending on who's the instructor.
Very disappointed with yoga class by Albert Tan, he basically just used the opportunity to showcase his advance yoga skills
Its not a class to show what he can do it should be a class to teach how to do different poses but he ended up skipping the basic and demo the advance poses.
Another occasion one friday lunch time i was the only member for Christine Tan class and she just asked if I had anything that i need to concentrate on and showed me a few poses then winded up the class in 15 minutes. I did not go all the way to attend a 15 minutes class.
Good yoga instructors that i hope will continue teaching are Ian Fung, Faiz, Dawn Tan and a few more.

name: Zhu Xue Song
review_text: Just yesterday, a fitness instructor with no trace of training pointed at my face, stared at me and said some very, very rude words to me because I occupied his stool and returned it. I was very scared at the time, I went to the bar to ask for help. It was 7:30 in the evening. I went to the bar to find a solution. The two beauties at the bar told me that all the people in charge were off work at that time. Then the reply to me was that there was no one, and the two of them gave me a smile that no one would care about if you complained. At this time, the fitness instructor with no trace of training came over again, stared at me, and pointed at me, as if to say If there is anything rude, it may be because many people are watching. The coach was very excited and made a  gesture towards me. Since he is not good at quarreling in crowded places, you win the customer, but you lose. The influence of the company, and many people nearby saw the performance of the fitness instructor. Will having such employees have a good impact on your company? Is this the professional quality of a fitness instructor that a high-end gym in Singapore should possess? Please conduct self-examination within your company.

review_text:
Getting lousier and lousier in service standards.
PT will rush other gym users to allow their trainees to use their machines....
Pay a bit more.. and you can use the premium services of pure fitness...
Consider jumping ship?
Have been a member for 5 years and fitness first is slowly degrading itself from a premium club to one that is on par with neighbour hood gyms.. feel sad!

name: Liz MA
review_text:
I have been a member for the past 4 months. I took the first month to assess the place and the people in it to make sure I am comfortable training there. The consultants, Johann and En En, are very friendly and patient in answering all my queries.
As I am entering my 50s, I took up the gym membership with specific goals in mind. I was recommended Herman to be my personal trainer. I am grateful that he is able to create a training programme to help me achieve my goals, without being too hard on me but yet still keep it challenging. He checks on me every time to make sure I am ok before and after my session. 4 months on, I have made considerable progress which motivates me to train regularly at the gym.
The gym is spacious and well-equipped. It has a big locker room and lounge area on the second floor. The toilet and shower rooms are kept clean always. The equipments are clean and well-maintained. I do not join the classes and I am not pressured to sign up for any, which is good.
Overall, I am comfortable there. If theres a room for improvement, it is to install a bidet in the toilet cubicles.

name: Azimah Muhamad
review_text:
I started personal training with Herman in June 2020. Herman starts training session with a well-being check to ensure I am well from injuries and recovery from previous training. At Fitness First Tampines, the Boditrax machine is available so we do have access to our muscle and fat % and other details. Herman tracks our trainings through a shared online form that we both can monitor that includes the above details. Slightly a year ago, I started training feeling 18kg kettlebell deadlift was challenging and now through training I am at 55kg barbell deadlift and hopefully to grow stronger.
Positive
Communication, Quality

review_text:
This is a very big branch as compared to the others I've went (West Gate, 100AM, Changi Biz Hub, Paya Lebar & AMK Hub).

Compared to them, this has also the biggest resting lounge area. The toilet and lounge and dance studio is on the second level while the rest of the gym is on the first.

The many treadmills had window view and TVs of international channels. (Westgate only has a pool view but no TV. Changi Biz hub had tv but the view outside the window was nothing much, AMK hub is basement so they only had TV, Paya Lebar only has window view and 100AM has no TV)

On top of that I feel that this Tampines branch has mainly every possible equipments which other branches lack. Kudos.
